**Summary:**
If the text in the first block of a gallery card is too large, a vertical scrollbar is displayed. This error appears because the preview text of the gallery card overflows the actual card.

**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**
1. add a new card to the gallery view
2. add a long text as a single block
3. reload the website
4. See error

**Screenshots:**
![bug](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35470146/128582221-85e46cb5-cb59-4abe-bc8d-22b1e9e17a0f.jpeg)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35470146/128582218-16dc6886-b05b-4891-8d24-dded725dfb0d.png)

**Platform:**
- Chrome 92.0.4515.131
- Firefox 89.0.2

**Additional context:**
Possible Fix (tested in Firefox and Chrome):
Add `overflow: hidden` to `focalboard/webapp/src/components/gallery/galleryCard.scss`

```diff
.focalboard-body .GalleryCard {
    position: relative;
    border: 1px solid rgba(var(--body-color), 0.09);
    border-radius: var(--default-rad);
    width: 280px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin-right: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
+   overflow: hidden;
	
    &.selected {
        background-color: rgba(90, 200, 255, 0.2);
    }

    &:hover {
        background-color: rgba(var(--body-color), 0.05);
        .optionsMenu {
            display: block;
        }
    }

    .optionsMenu {
        background-color: rgb(var(--main-bg));
        border-radius: var(--default-rad);
        display: none;
        position: absolute;
        right: 10px;
        top: 10px;
        z-index: 30;
